Edition:
Quote:  Several sealers lived permanently on the Chathams because there was no law there as the group only nominally belonged to England and was not yet a part of New Zealand. It was the home of escaped convicts, ne'er-do-wells and beachcombers from Australia chiefly, but those with the worst reputation came from Callao in Peru.
